          "body": "## Context\n\nDiscovered while scaffolding `pd-ocr-trainer-spa` (ocr-container-meta retirement plan #282).\n\n`pd-book-tools` declares `torch` (and `python-doctr` / `torchvision`) as hard `[project.dependencies]`. Every `pd-*` repo depends on `pd-book-tools`, so multi-GB torch lands in the dependency closure of every consumer — including FastAPI web processes that never run a model.\n\nThe `pd-ocr-trainer-spa` design decision **D-T1** wants the long-lived FastAPI web process to be torch-free; it imports only torch-free config models. But torch still enters `pd-ocr-trainer-spa`'s pip closure transitively via `pd-book-tools` → `pd-ocr-ops` → SPA. So \"torch-free web process\" currently holds only for *runtime imports*, not the install closure — every `uv tool install pd-ocr-trainer-spa` pulls multi-GB torch.\n\n## Proposal\n\nMirror what `pd-ocr-training` already did: move `torch` / `python-doctr` / `torchvision` (and any other heavy ML-only deps) out of `[project.dependencies]` into an optional extra, e.g.:\n\n```toml\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nocr = [\"python-doctr\", \"torch\", \"torchvision\"]\n```\n\n(extra name TBD — `ocr` / `doctr` / `ml`, whatever fits the API surface).\n\nThen ensure the **torch-free import path works**:\n- `import pd_book_tools` and the light data-model / layout / utility names must import with torch absent.\n- Modules that genuinely need torch/DocTR (the OCR engine wrappers) must be import-guarded or lazily loaded, so accessing them without the extra raises a helpful `ImportError` (\"install `pd-book-tools[ocr]`\") rather than a raw `ModuleNotFoundError` at package import.\n- Add a test (subprocess with torch hidden) asserting the torch-free surface imports clean.\n\nReference implementation: `pd-ocr-training` did exactly this — `torch`/DocTR behind a `[train]` extra, `__init__.py` restructured so the torch-free Protocol + config models import without torch, heavy names resolved lazily via module `__getattr__`.\n\n## Impact\n\nThis is a foundational change — `pd-book-tools` is the dependency root for the whole suite, so the import-surface restructuring needs care. But it is the only way the suite's FastAPI web processes get a genuinely torch-free install closure.\n\nTracks: (none yet)",
